SIMPLE: totem
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Totem
<hw>To"tem</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Massachusetts Indian
<ets>wutohtimoin</ets> that to which a person or place belongs.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A rude picture, as of a bird, beast, or the like, used
by the North American Indians as a symbolic designation, as of a family
or a clan; also, the object or animal itself, considered as an symbol of
the family.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And they painted on the grave posts⟦br⟧
Of the graves, yet unforgotten,⟦br⟧
Each his own ancestral <qex>totem</qex>⟦br⟧
Each the symbol of his household;⟦br⟧
Figures of the bear and reindeer,⟦br⟧
Of the turtle, crane, and beaver.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>totem</qex>, the clan deity, the beast or bird who in
some supernatural way attends to the clan and watches over it.</q>
<rj><qau>Bagehot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anything which serves as a venerated or mystic
symbol or emblem.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Totemic</ent>⟦br⟧
